Anonymous Sun 11 Apr 2021 01:16:17 No.37813246 Report
Quoted By: >>37813279
>>37812092
>Is it one complete series focusing on her and her humie?
For the most part, yeah. Also occasionally focuses on other Cauthan (the cat people) and their relationships with each other, but the main character and his cat lady never separate from one another and have a very loving relationship.

(The main character also has an advanced AI that has come to love him too, and in the most recent chapters she's managed to build herself a body and it looks like it *might* lead to them being a thruple between main character, cat lady, and sentient AI-turned-cyborg, but at this point it's definitely not the case)

Only qualm I personally have with the story is admittedly a dumb one; the AI manages to be able to perfectly translate the alien language over the course of... Thirty seconds when in reality being able to translate between any given language upon first contact would take months if not years. It doesn't matter how quickly the AI can parse data; it's a matter of how much of the language they're actually exposed to. It can't translate a word it's never heard, after all, and there's no way in fucking hell that the AI heard every word in the Cauthan language in every possible context over the course of less than a minute.

It actually would have been a good sub-plot if it took longer for the language to be translated; then there could be moments where there are mutual understandings/resolutions, mutual learning, and stuff like that. Unfortunately all of that was tossed to the wayside for the sake of convenience.
